  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Given two points ($x_1$, $y_1$, $z_1$) and ($x_2$, $y_2$, $z_2$) in three dimensional space, the Manhattan distance between those points is defined as $|x_1 - x_2| + |y_1 - y_2| + |z_1 - z_2|$.</p>\n<p>Let $C(r)$ be a sphere with radius $r$ and center in the origin $O(0, 0, 0)$.</p>\n<p>Let $I(r)$ be the set of all points with integer coordinates on the surface of $C(r)$.</p>\n<p>Let $S(r)$ be the sum of the Manhattan distances of all elements of $I(r)$ to the origin $O$.</p>\n<p>E.g. $S(45)=34518$.</p>\n<p>Find $S({10}^{10})$.</p>\n</section>",
